<div class="col-md-8 col-sm-8 col-xs-12 " style="text-align:left">
  <% if @user == current_user %>
    <p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>
    <%= form_for @book, :html => {:multipart => true} do |f| %>
      <% if @book.errors.any? %> 
        This Error message isn't working
        <div id="error_explanation">
          <h2><%= pluralize(@book.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this book from being saved:</h2>
          <ul>
            <% @book.errors.full_messages.each do |msg| %>
              <li><%= msg %></li>
            <% end %>
          </ul>
        </div>
      <% end %>

      <%= render 'shared/error_messages' %>
      <center><span class="Body-C5">Enter Book info (items with * are required)</span></center> 
      <%= f.hidden_field :user_id %>

      <div class="blacktxt" >
        <div style="float:left;width:75%;">
          <b>* Book title </b></div>
        <div style="float:right;width:25%;">
          Genre <br></div>
      </div>
      <div class="profilebox" >
        <div style="float:left;width:75%;">
          <%= f.text_area :title, :cols => 50, :rows => 2, placeholder: "Book title" %>
        </div>
        <div style="float:right;width:25%;">
          <%= f.text_area :genre, :cols => 15, :rows => 1, placeholder: "Genre" %>
        </div><br>
      </div><br><br>

      <div class="blacktxt" >
        <br><b>Price </b>(in USD) $<%= f.text_field :price, placeholder: "4.99" %><br>
        <br>Book jacket blurb (2000 characters max)<br>
      </div>
      <div class="profilebox" >
        <%= f.text_area :blurb, :cols => 70, :rows => 6, placeholder: "Book jacket blurb" %>
      </div>
      <span class="blurbcount"></span><br>
      <div class="blacktxt">
        Sentence about book (140 characters max) 
      </div>
      <div class="profilebox" >
        <%= f.text_area :fiftychar, :cols => 70, :rows => 1, placeholder: "Brief sentence about book - MUST be less than 140 characters" %>
      </div>
      <span class="charcount"></span><br>

      <div class="blacktxt" >
        Date book is estimated to be or was released
        <%= f.date_select :releasedate %>
        <br>Upload a picture of the bookcover (.jpg, .gif, .jpeg, or .png)
        <br><%= f.file_field :coverpic %> OR <br>
        URL for a picture of your book cover
        <%= f.text_area :coverpicurl, :cols => 70, :rows => 1, placeholder: "URL to a PICTURE of bookcover (must end in .jpg, .gif, .jpeg, or .png)" %><br> The easiest way to obtain the URL is to go to a site that has a picture of your book cover, right click on the PICTURE, select Copy IMAGE url, and paste here. This MUST include the 'http://' part of the URL in order to work. DO NOT PASTE A URL TO A webSITE. Only PICTURES with urls that end in .JPG, .JPEG, .PNG, or .GIF will work.  
        We recommend uploading files for ALL 3 of the following formats (so your customers have more options for the type of ereader they own)<br><br>
        <div style="float:left;width:70%;">
          Upload your ebook, as a pdf (for iBooks, PCs, & Kobo) </div>
        <div style="float:right;width:30%;">
          <%= f.file_field :bookpdf %> </div><br>
        <div style="float:left;width:70%;">
          Upload your ebook, as a mobi (for Kindle) </div>
        <div style="float:right;width:30%;">
          <%= f.file_field :bookmobi %> </div><br>
        <div style="float:left;width:70%;">
          Upload your ebook, as an epub (for Adobe, Nook, & Sony kobo) </div>
        <div style="float:right;width:30%;">
          <%= f.file_field :bookepub %> </div><br>
        <br>If you have a video about your brand on <b>YouTube</b>, go to that video's page. Underneath the video, click on <i>Share</i> then click on <i>Embed</i>. Copy the code that appears and paste to replace the default code below. <br /> 
        Video 1: <br>
      </div>
      <div class="profilebox" >
        <%= f.text_area :youtube1, :cols => 70, :rows => 2, placeholder: '<iframe width="420" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/frlviTJcVUo" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>' %>
      <div class="blacktxt">
        <br> Video 2: <br /> 
      </div>
      <div class="profilebox" >
        <%= f.text_area :youtube2, :cols => 70, :rows => 2, placeholder: '<iframe width="420" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/frlviTJcVUo" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>' %>
      </div>

  <%= f.submit "Save New Book" %>
<% end %>

<br>There are a few situations where book information will fail to save. If you are having trouble saving your book info, please check for these errors: <br>
1. Uploading a file that is not .pdf in the iBook/PC info field, or not a .mobi for Kindle, etc. <br>
2. Uploading a file that is not .jpg, .gif, .jpeg, or .png in the book cover field <br>
3. Entering a URL that does not end in .jpg, .gif, .jpeg, or .png for a picture of your book cover (this URL is not used if you upload a picture of your book cover, so no need to do both) <br>
4. Entering more than 140 characters into the field for Sentence about book <br>
5. Entering more than 2000 characters into the field for Book jacket blurb <br>
